By Yusuf Yunus  Ikeja  –  The Nigerian Airspace Management Agency (NAMA) has cautioned its staff to ensure full compliance with the directives and safety guidelines issued by the Federal Government ahead of the easing of the COVID-19 lockdown on Monday. Its Managing Director, Capt. Fola Akinkuotu, gave the advice in a statement issued on Sunday in Lagos. Akinkuotu said the workers should adhere strictly to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on COVID-19 preventive measures, including social distancing, regular washing of and/ or sanitising of hands and wearing of face masks. “While the health and wellbeing of workers is of utmost importance to management, a lot needs to be done by the workers to ensure they remain safe in the face of the Covid-19 pandemic which is still very much in our midst. “We are also assuring our staff that the agency has put in place procedures and measures that would guarantee their safety in the work place,” he said. Akinkuotu noted that the battle against Covid-19 was a collective one and they must all join hands with the federal government to triumph at the end of the day. (NAN) Tolu Aiyegbusi Abuja - The Nigeria Postal Services (NIPOST) says it is still at the forefront providing essential services in the country amidst the lockdown due to Conivarius pandemic This is stated in a statement signed and made available to News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Friday by NIPOST General… May 1, 2020 In "News" Executive Orders: NAMA Challenges Airspace Managers On Strict Compliance June 19, 2017 In "News" \Dr Bashir Jamoh, NIMASA DG LAGOS - The Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency (NIMASA) has extended the validity of Statutory and Trading certificates for all Nigerian Registered vessels. These include Standards of Training, Certification and Watchkeeping (STCW) certificates for seafarers issued by the Agency. The Director-General of NIMASA, Dr.… April 16, 2020 In "NIMASA & Maritime"